SPRINT 4 PLANNING HERE:
User stories:
As a student/developer, I want: The app to remain stable when updated, without introducing regressions.
As a student, I want to be able to sign up/log in through the website to create my account (8 US) (Chandler)
As a student, I want to be able to view my profile details (including my tickets, calendar) (Reema & Chandler)
As a student, I want to be able to scroll through events to eventually purchase a ticket for one (5 US) (Chandler)

As a student, I want to be able to log out to protect my private information (Reema)
As a student, I want to be able to view the events I’m attending on a calendar view and to add them to my personal calendar.  (Chandler, Rim)
As a student, I want to view a dedicated 'My Tickets' page with unique QR codes for each event, so that I can easily present my ticket for check-in. (13 US) (Rim)
​​As a student, I want to export event details to my personal calendar application (like Google Calendar or Outlook), so that I do not miss events I am attending. (3 US) (Rim)
As a student, I want to see a live countdown timer on my ticket cards, so that I have a visual reminder of how much time remains until the event starts. (3 US) (Rim)

******
As an organizer, I want to be able to create and login to my organizer account [Sunidhi]
As an organizer, I want to be able to create and edit events visible to the public (through home page) [Sunidhi]
As an organizer, I want to be able to view my analytics for every event [Sunidhi]
As an organizer, I want filters in my dashboard, so that I can quickly access relevant events. (3 US) [Sunidhi]
As an organizer, I want to see an approval status dialog when my organization is pending or denied, so that I understand why I can't create events. [Sunidhi]
As an organizer, I want to scan student QR codes or enter IDs manually to validate tickets in real-time, so that I can track attendance accurately. (5 US) [Rim, Sunidhi]
As an organizer, I want to be able to view and edit my profile. [Sunidhi, Patricia]


********
As an administrator, I want to be able to log in as an administrator [Sunidhi]
As an administrator, I want to be able to view current accounts of students (Reema, Sunidhi)
As an administrator, I want to be able to view current accounts of organizers (Reema, Sunidhi)
As an administrator, I want to be able to accept/refuse new organizers account [Sunidhi]
As an administrator, I want to view comprehensive platform analytics showing user counts, ticket sales, and attendee check-ins, so that I can monitor overall system health. [Sunidhi, Patricia]
As an admin, I want role-based page access control so that only authenticated users with the correct role can view protected pages. [Sunidhi]


******
As a user, I want to see different menu options based on my login status, so that the interface reflects my access level. [Chandler] (5 US)
As a user, I want my login to redirect me to the correct dashboard (student/organizer/admin), so that I only see features relevant to my role. (5 US) 

*********
As a developer, I want to be able to want complete system diagrams (architecture, flow, class, block), so that the whole team understands the system structure and future work is easier. (3  US)

