User Story #35: Edit Profile & API error UX (Assignee: Chandler) [US 3] [Status: DONE]
Tasks:
Prefill Edit Profile form immediately from server-side user data on page load.
Apply and preserve local overrides (localStorage) if server is unreachable.
Handle PATCH errors (405, 4xx, 5xx) with friendly user-facing messages; do not display raw server dumps.
Add a small inline error/notification area on profile and edit pages for friendly messages.
Ensure Profile page displays a visible, working “Log Out” link when signed-in (clears cookies/localStorage and updates UI).
Acceptance Tests:
Opening Edit Profile shows server values in each field within 200ms (or immediately after fetch) — local overrides appear if present.
Submitting profile updates shows “Profile updated” on success; on failure shows “Couldn’t update profile — please try again.”
A 405 response from PATCH surfaces a clear message like “Update not allowed — contact support.”
Clicking “Log Out” clears authentication cookies/localStorage and returns the UI to the logged-out state; the nav updates and protected links hide.

Result: PASS



User Story #36: Signup/Login/Profile fixes (Assignee: Chandler) [US 8] [Status: DONE]
Tasks:
Make Student ID visible on signup and save it on account creation.
Ensure signup sends separate first_name and last_name (no blank last name).
Ensure email is stored only in email; username is a distinct field.
Make login handler respect the credential the UI requests (email or username) and show consistent UX.
Replace raw error dumps with friendly messages for duplicate-account and other signup/login failures.
Add basic client-side validation (required fields, email format, student ID pattern)

Acceptance Tests:
Filling Student ID on signup results in the Student ID appearing on the Profile page after account creation.
Signing up populates first_name and last_name fields on the server 
Email is present only in the email field; username is a separate, distinct value.
Login succeeds username and password; Error messages display when there is a failure.
Attempting to create a duplicate account shows a short message: “An account with this email already exists.”.

Result: PASS 


